### [Psalms Chapter 39](../../../bib/kjv/psa039.htm#001.md)

[Psalms](../../../bib/kjv/psa001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">psa 39:0</span></span>

Overview

[Psa 39:1](../../../bib/kjv/psa039.htm#001.md), David's care of this
thoughts; [Psa 39:4](../../../bib/kjv/psa039.htm#004.md), The consideration
of the brevity and vanity of life; [Psa
39:7](../../../bib/kjv/psa039.htm#007.md), the reverence of God's
judgments, [Psa 39:10](../../../bib/kjv/psa039.htm#010.md), and prayer, are
his bridles of impatience.

Jeduthun, probably the same as Ethan, [Ch1
6:44](../../../bib/kjv/ch1006.htm#044.md), was one of the sons of Merari,
and is supposed to have been one the four masters of music, or leaders
of bands, belonging to the temple service. It is therefore probable that
David, having composed this Psalm, gave it to Jeduthun and his company
to sing; and it is very likely, that it was written on the same occasion
as the preceding. [Psa 62:1](../../../bib/kjv/psa062.htm#001.md), [Psa
77:1](../../../bib/kjv/psa077.htm#001.md) \*titles [Ch1
16:41](../../../bib/kjv/ch1016.htm#041.md), [Ch1
25:1-6](../../../bib/kjv/ch1025.htm#001.md)

